gurmukhi: nmo biR`D bu`DM krI jog juAwlw ]
transliteration: Namo Briddh Buddhan Daroo Jog Juaalaa||
translation: O the blazer of Yoga-fire, the manifestation of supreme wisdom,

gurmukhi: nmo cMf muMfI miRVw kRUr kwlw ]22]241]
transliteration: Namo Channd Mounndoo Mridaa Kroor Kaalaa||22||241||
translation: The destroyer of Chand and Munda and performer of the heinous action of crushing their dead bodies ! I salute Thee.22.241.
Thou art the bestower of bliss by destroying the great sinners.

gurmukhi: nmo dwVH gwVHw DrI du`K hrxI ]
transliteration: Namo Daadh Gadhdaa Ddaroo Doukkh Harnoo||
translation: Thou art the remover of the anguish of saints by destroying the tyrants with Thy dreadful teeth.

gurmukhi: nmo swsqR byqw nmo ssqR gwmI ]
transliteration: Namo Saastra Betaa Namo Sastra Gadmoond|
translation: Thou art the knower of Shastras, knower of the use of weapons;

gurmukhi: nmo j`C ib`idAw DrI pUrx kwmI ]23]242]
transliteration: Namo Jachchh Biddiaa Ddaroo Puran Kaamoond|23||242||
translation: Perfect in knowledge of Yakshas, and the fulfiller of the desires! I salute Thee.23.242.
O the giver of suffering to the enemies, all the people worship Thee.
Thou art the creator of all interests and also their destroyer.
Thou art the power of Hanuman;
Thou art Kalika and manifestation of the sword and wielder of the power in Thy own hands ! I salute thee.24.243.
O the masterly power of Hanuman ! Thou art the goddess of Nagarkot (Kangra);
Thou art the manifestation of Kama (love). Thou art Kamakhya, the goddess.
And the bestower of bliss on al like kalratri (Kali);
O the bestower of the great miraculous powers and wealth and wielder of the sword! I salute Thee.25.244.
